default9.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCost-benefitsdefault9.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAny restriction on young people’s access to lega
defaultl advice is highly unlikely to be good value for money for the tax-payer. Robust research has shown that a typical young person with a civil legal problem costs local health services, housing 
defaultservices and social services around £13,000 if they cannot recei
defaultve early advice.
default In addition, clear links have been established between young people’s unresolved civil legal problems and increased criminal offending.
default 
